      "side": 1,
      "message": "Bullet points are good here\n\nRefs are git refs to pull commits from when displaying the console.\nAccepted formats include:\n* An explicit ref: e.g. \"refs/heads/master\"\n* A regular expression.  e.g. \"regexp:refs/branch-heads/\\d+\\.\\d+\"\nThe regular expression must:\n  * Start with \"regexp:\"\n  * Contain two forward slashes\n  * Not start with ^ or end with $\n\nAlso add limitations:\nA maximum of 100 total refs are supported.  \nIf after expanding the ref regexs, there are more than 100 refs, the console may fail to load.",
